  <body>

  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODE</xref>
 is a code which identifies an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
 uniquely.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODES</xref>
 are managed by:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Organisation_Data_Service</xref>
         <p>
 (
            <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">ODS</xref>
)      </p>
      </li>
      <li>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_prescription_services">NHS Prescription Services</xref>
      </li>
      <li>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_dental_services">NHS Dental Services</xref>
         <p>.</p>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/organisation_data_service.asp"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">Organisation_Data_Service</xref>
            <p>
codes can be downloaded from 
                <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/technology_reference_data_update_distribution_(trud).asp"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">Technology_Reference_Data_Update_Distribution_(TRUD)</xref>
            </p>
